  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hope for Farming, Rural Livelihoods and Food Sovereignty with Families in Rural Manabi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented by three rural, second-tier organizations located in Ecuador&#x2019;s central zone. Small-farm production and agricultural diversity are jeopardized by the corn and rice monoculture, which are highly dependant on agrochemicals. Because it is difficult to make a living from small-farm production, youth and rural people have migrated to cities seeking better opportunities. This has weakened the organizations&#x2019; structures and capacity to make proposals. This project will strengthen organizational structure at the provincial and regional levels, develop actions in policy and organizational advocacy within the framework of food sovereignty and improve household economies by encouraging agroecology on small family farms and promoting local associative marketing of surplus produce. In total, 240 families will receive original resources and another 240 will receive resources from passing on the gift by the year 2013.</narrative>
  </description>
